                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/258: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-01-05T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Your telegram no. 3 of January 3, 4 p.m. Considering the statement by Mr.
                    Barnes Moss, is it the feeling of the Legation that it still would be wise to
                    make such a communication to the Japanese Chargé here as the Department
                    indicated in its telegram of December 28, 4 p.m., no. 299?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
